// -------------------------------------------------------read the data objects till the openflow/networking part
val rid_disctime__cpuutil = VmCPUUtil.calculatePeriodAvgPerRidFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime).map(s => ((s._1, s._2._1), s._2._2.toDouble)).coalesce(10)
val rid_disctime__diskrb = VmDiskReadByte.calculateDerivativePerRidFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime).coalesce(10)
val rid_disctime__diskwb = VmDiskWriteByte.calculateDerivativePerRidFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime).coalesce(10)
val rid_disctime__netinbyte = VmNetIncomingByte.calculateDerivativePerRidFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime).coalesce(10)
val rid_disctime__netoutbyte = VmNetOutgoingByte.calculateDerivativePerRidFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime).coalesce(10)




  
  
  

  
  

// -------------------------------------------------------read the networking data objects
val commPairDisctimeBwutil = OFFlowBw.calculatePeriodAvgPerCommPairFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime)
val macToRid = Utils.getMacToVMRid(sqlContext)
val ridToId = Utils.getVMRidToID(sqlContext)
val idToRid = ridToId.map(ri => (ri._2.toLong, ri._1))

// (rid, (mac, id))
val ridToMacId = macToRid.map(mr => (mr._2, mr._1)).join(ridToId)
val macToId = ridToMacId.map(rmi => rmi._2)

// produce (source Mac, ((des MAC, (discrete_time, average bandwidth)), srcVMid))
val convertedSrcMac = commPairDisctimeBwutil.map(p => (p._1, (p._2, p._3))).join(macToId)

// produce (dst Mac, ((srcVMId, (discrete_time, average bandwidth)), dstVMId))
val convertedSrcDstMac = convertedSrcMac.map(p => (p._2._1._1, (p._2._2, p._2._1._2))).join(macToId)

//((srcVMId, dstVMId, discrete_time), BW)
val idToIdDisctimeBw = convertedSrcDstMac.map(p => ((p._2._1._1, p._2._2, p._2._1._2._1), p._2._1._2._2))
  .reduceByKey((a, b) => a+b)

// Produce ((rid, dt), value)
val sendBWDisctimeBW = idToIdDisctimeBw
  .map(p => ((p._1._1, p._1._3), p._2))
  .reduceByKey((a, b) => a+b)
  .map(f => (f._1._1, (f._1._2, f._2)))
  .join(idToRid)//(id, ((dt, value), rid))
  .map(f => ((f._2._2, f._2._1._1), f._2._1._2))

// Produce ((rid, dt), value)
val receiveBWDisctimeBW = idToIdDisctimeBw
  .map(p => ((p._1._2, p._1._3), p._2))
  .reduceByKey((a, b) => a+b)
  .map(f => (f._1._1, (f._1._2, f._2)))
  .join(idToRid)//(id, ((dt, value), rid))
  .map(f => ((f._2._2, f._2._1._1), f._2._1._2))
  
  
//-------------------------------------------------join the data objects
val rid_dt__2:RDD[((String, Long), Array[Double])] = rid_disctime__cpuutil.join(rid_disctime__diskrb)
      .filter(s => s._2._1.isInstanceOf[Double] && s._2._2.isInstanceOf[Double])
      .map(s => (s._1, Array[Double](s._2._1, s._2._2)))

val rid_dt__3:RDD[((String, Long), Array[Double])] = rid_dt__2.join(rid_disctime__diskwb)
  .map(s => (s._1, s._2._1 :+ s._2._2))

val rid_dt__4:RDD[((String, Long), Array[Double])] = rid_dt__3.join(rid_disctime__netinbyte)
  .map(s => (s._1, s._2._1 :+ s._2._2))

val rid_dt__5:RDD[((String, Long), Array[Double])] = rid_dt__4.join(rid_disctime__netoutbyte)
  .map(s => (s._1, s._2._1 :+ s._2._2))

val rid_dt__6:RDD[((String, Long), Array[Double])] = rid_dt__5.join(receiveBWDisctimeBW)
  .map(s => (s._1, s._2._1 :+ s._2._2))

val rid_dt__7:RDD[((String, Long), Array[Double])] = rid_dt__6.join(sendBWDisctimeBW)
  .map(s => (s._1, s._2._1 :+ s._2._2))
  
  
  
//-----------------------------------------------some processing needed for the graph generation
val ridIdJoin = rid_dt__7.map(s => (s._1._1, (s._1._2, s._2))).join(ridToId)
val idDtData = ridIdJoin.map(s => ((s._2._2,s._2._1._1), s._2._1._2))
//(time,(Array,id))
val DtDataid = idDtData.map(s => (s._1._2,(s._2,s._1._1)))
//(time,(id,Array))
val DtidData = idDtData.map(s => (s._1._2,(s._1._1,s._2)))
//(time,((srcid,destid),BW))
val DtSrcIdDstIdBW = idToIdDisctimeBw.map(s => (s._1._3,((s._1._1,s._1._2),s._2)))


// **** Section 3 Generate physical server ****
val rawPmnameAvgCPU = PhysicalVirtualMemoryPercentage.calculateAvgFromFile(sqlContext, hdfspaths, startTime, endTime)
val pmnameAvgCPU = rawPmnameAvgCPU.map(p => (p._1.split("_").filter(s => !s.equals("server")).mkString("_"), p._2))
val pmnameAvgCPUFormatted = pmnameAvgCPU.map(pm => (Utils.murmurHash(pm._1, 123).longValue()*10000000, pm._1, pm._2, "phyMachine"))
//debug
//    pmnameAvgCPU.collect().foreach(println)

// **** Section 4 Generate physical server to vm relation ****
val vmidToPhy = Utils.getVMIdToPhyServer(sqlContext)
val vmidToPhyEdge = vmidToPhy.map(vmpm => (vmpm._1, Utils.murmurHash(vmpm._2, 123).longValue()*10000000, 0.0, "host"))

%pyspark def cleanfile(filename): ret_dict = {} with open(filename) as f: graph_list = [] for line in f: ## get the key t_key = "" for x in line: if x == "(": pass elif x == ",": break else: t_key += x ## list of preprocessed vertices list_vert = str(line).split("Vetrex") ## list of preprocessed edges list_edges = str(list_vert[-1]).split("edge") ## update last element in vertices list_vert[-1] = list_edges[0] list_vert = list_vert[1:] list_edges = list_edges[1:] ## dict of vertices and edges vert_dict = {} edge_list = [] for v in list_vert: ed_v = v list_chs = " ()List" for x in list_chs: ed_v = ed_v.replace(x,"") if ed_v[0] == ",": ed_v = ed_v[1:] if ed_v[-1] == ",": ed_v = ed_v[:-1] ded_v = ed_v.split(",") vkey = ded_v[0] vval = ded_v[1].split(".") vert_dict[vkey] = vval for e in list_edges: ed_e = e list_chs = " ()\n" for x in list_chs: ed_e = ed_e.replace(x,"") if ed_e[0] == ",": ed_e = ed_e[1:] if ed_e[-1] == ",": ed_e = ed_e[:-1] eval = ed_e.split(",") edge_list.append(eval) ret_tuple = (t_key,[vert_dict,edge_list]) graph_list.append(ret_tuple) return graph_list #print(t_key) #print(list_vert[0]) #print(list_vert[1]) #print(list_vert[-1]) #print(list_edges[0]) #print(list_edges[1]) #print(list_edges[-1]) #print("Step 1") #print(ed_v) #print(ded_v) #print(vkey) #print(vval) #print("Step 2") #print(ed_e) #print(eval) def cleanfile_PHY_VM(filename): ret_dict = {} with open(filename) as f: G=nx.Graph() for line in f: l = line[1:-1] l = l.split(",") G.add_edge(l[0],l[1]) return G def build_graph(g_dict): # function to build graph, input is a list of vert_dict and list_edge G=nx.DiGraph() for v in g_dict[0].keys(): G.add_node(v) for e in g_dict[1]: G.add_edge(e[0],e[1]) return G def process_graph(G): return nx.degree_centrality(G) def show(p): img = StringIO.StringIO() p.savefig(img, format='svg') img.seek(0) print "%html
" + img.buf + "
" def get_sensitivity(list_compo,VM_PHY_Graph): list_nearest = [] for comp in list_compo: nearest = [] for v in comp: nearest.extend(list(nx.all_neighbors(VM_PHY_Graph,v))) list_nearest.append(set(nearest)) sens_list = [] for i in range(len(list_nearest)): for j in range(i,len(list_nearest),1): sens_list.append((i,j,len(list_nearest[i].intersection(list_nearest[j])) )) return sens_list

%pyspark ## Plot the mean centrality import matplotlib matplotlib.use('Agg') import matplotlib.pyplot as plt; plt.rcdefaults() import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import StringIO def show(p): img = StringIO.StringIO() p.savefig(img, format='svg') img.seek(0) print "%html
" + img.buf + "
" plt.figure() # Example data bins = numpy.linspace(0, 4, 10) plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: s[1][0][2]).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App1') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: s[1][1][2]).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App2') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: s[1][2][2]).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App3') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: s[1][3][2]).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App4') # plt.barh(y_pos, performance, xerr=error, align='center', alpha=0.4) plt.xlabel('Frequency') plt.xlabel('Connectivity') plt.title('Connectivity(number of nodes to disconnect)') plt.legend(loc='upper right') show(plt) plt.savefig("/home/ubuntu/connectivity.png")

" + img.buf + "

%pyspark ## Plot the mean centrality import matplotlib matplotlib.use('Agg') import matplotlib.pyplot as plt; plt.rcdefaults() import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import StringIO def show(p): img = StringIO.StringIO() p.savefig(img, format='svg') img.seek(0) print "%html
" + img.buf + "
" plt.figure() # Example data bins = numpy.linspace(0, 2.2, 100) plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][0][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App1') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][1][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App2') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][2][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App3') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][3][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App4') # plt.barh(y_pos, performance, xerr=error, align='center', alpha=0.4) plt.xlabel('Frequency') plt.xlabel('Mean degree Centrality') plt.title('Mean degree centrality for the top 4 Apps') plt.legend(loc='upper center') show(plt) plt.savefig("/home/ubuntu/mean_deg_centr.png") plt.figure() # Example data bins = numpy.linspace(0, 2.2, 100) plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][0][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App1') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][1][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App2') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][2][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App3') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][3][5].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App4') # plt.barh(y_pos, performance, xerr=error, align='center', alpha=0.4) plt.xlabel('Frequency') plt.xlabel('Max degree Centrality') plt.title('Max degree centrality for the top 4 Apps') plt.legend(loc='upper center') show(plt) plt.savefig("/home/ubuntu/max_deg_centr.png")

%pyspark ## Plot the mean centrality import matplotlib matplotlib.use('Agg') import matplotlib.pyplot as plt; plt.rcdefaults() import numpy as np import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import StringIO def show(p): img = StringIO.StringIO() p.savefig(img, format='svg') img.seek(0) print "%html
" + img.buf + "
" plt.figure() # Example data bins = numpy.linspace(0, 1.5, 100) plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][0][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App1') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][1][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App2') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][2][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App3') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: numpy.mean(s[1][3][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App4') # plt.barh(y_pos, performance, xerr=error, align='center', alpha=0.4) plt.xlabel('Frequency') plt.xlabel('Mean load Centrality') plt.title('Mean load centrality for the top 4 Apps') plt.legend(loc='upper center') show(plt) plt.savefig("/home/ubuntu/mean_load_centr.png") plt.figure() # Example data bins = numpy.linspace(0, 1.5, 100) plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][0][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App1') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][1][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App2') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][2][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App3') plt.hist(graph_strongly_connected_components_graph_atrributes.map(lambda s: max(s[1][3][8].values())).collect(), bins, alpha=0.5, label='App4') # plt.barh(y_pos, performance, xerr=error, align='center', alpha=0.4) plt.xlabel('Frequency') plt.xlabel('Max load Centrality') plt.title('Max load centrality for the top 4 Apps') plt.legend(loc='upper center') show(plt) plt.savefig("/home/ubuntu/mean_load_centr.png")

" + img.buf + "
" fig = plt.figure() for x in graph_sens_list.take(1)[0]: plt.scatter(x[0]+1, x[1]+1) plt.text(x[0]+1, x[1]+1, str(x[2]), color="red", fontsize=16) # plt.barh(y_pos, performance, xerr=error, align='center', alpha=0.4) plt.xlim(0, 5) plt.ylim(0, 5) plt.xlabel('App Index') plt.ylabel('App Index') plt.title('PHY connectivity between Apps') plt.legend(loc='upper center') show(plt) plt.savefig("/home/ubuntu/phy_sens.png")
